      "date": "2011-04-08 03:42:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nthe existing patch in b1_8 contains several problems,\n1, in mount_facet, \"do_facet\" will look for the host of the active\nfacet, but the $(facet_host ${facet}) used by the patch won't\ntake it into account.\n\n2, remote_node should only take one host as its argument, and\nfurthermore, the do_rpc_nods already deal with the case of \nremote nodes\n\nhow about the following one,\n\nset_default_debug_facet() {\n    local HOST=`facet_active_host $1`\n    [ -z $HOST ] && echo No host defined for facet $1 && exit 1\n    do_rpc_nodes $HOST set_default_debug\n}\n\nset_default_debug_nodes() {\n    local nodes=$1\n    do_rpc_nodes $nodes set_default_debug\n}",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
